commit.message: ci: simplify artifacts directory for release publishing workflow

ci: output cargo-c version and simplify building the C library for releases

Always use the git repo, checking out a tag for releases or a given
branch name. Also, use the release-strip profile to match the binary
pkgcraft-c release files.
ci: upload all release files to pypi in the same action

ci: use distinct artifact names for arch target wheels

To fix issues using the upload and download artifact actions v4.

Revert "ci: strip bundled pkgcraft-c library for releases"

The bundled pkgcraft-c Cargo.toml doesn't support the release-strip
profile yet, only the pkgcraft workspace does.

This reverts commit bbe8d73bac76ba28ec50185ce3cd603d66b36573.
setup: bump pkgcraft-c version
benches: fix dep parsing benchmark
dep: add initial Cpn object support for pkgcraft changes
tox: disable running doctests from all envs
tox: disable doctests until upstream issue with pytest-8 is fixed

dep: update 'slot' to 'slot_dep' for dep field attr naming

To match pkgcraft changes.
config: update for pkgcraft_config_repos_set() format arg change

Since pkgcraft now uses the provided custom cache dir for metadata
verification as well.

repo: support custom metadata cache path for ebuild repo regen
